`,n.jsx(e.h2,{children:"Introduction"}),`
`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:'IIT Madras hosts one of Indias most interdisciplinary campuses, blending engineering, data science, sustainability, and deep-tech entrepreneurship through its research park. The summer internship track is prized because interns often work inside active industrial collaborations or translational labs. All dates and stipend cues here are "Expected / Indicative"they mirror 2024/2025 behavior to help you move before announcements land.'}),`
`,n.jsx(e.h2,{children:"About the Institute"}),`
`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"Located in Chennais Taramani ecosystem, IIT Madras routinely tops national rankings and operates Indias first university-based research park. Labs like Robert Bosch Centre for Data Science and AI (RBCDSAI), Centre for Innovation (CFI), and advanced manufacturing facilities make IITM attractive to both theory-heavy and build-heavy profiles. Compare the rest of the IIT network at the IIT internships hub to see how Madras differs on depth and industry proximity."}),`
`,n.jsx(e.h2,{children:"Overview of Summer Internship Programme 2026"}),`
`,n.jsx(e.p,{children:"Expect a 68 week engagement beginning mid-May. Interns onboard with faculty mentors, receive a scoped project, and iterate through weekly reviews. Deliverables often include a prototype, dataset with analysis, or a technical paper draft. Certificates are routine; credit transfer is rare. High performers may be invited to continue as project staff or to extend their work into a semester project with the same lab."}),`
